Required Bioinformatic Tools:
  GATK
  BWA
  Picard

Required  yum install packages 
	yum install openssl openssl-devel 
	yum install epel-release 
	yum install gcc
	yum install gcc-c++
	yum install freetype freetype-devel libpng-devel
	yum install collectl
	yum install sysstat
	yum install strace 
	yum install gnuplot
If python is not being installed by source install the packages below.
	yum install python-pip python-wheel
	yum install python-devel 

Python 
Python 3 and two of its packages are needed to run the pipeline scripts. If not already installed, you can install python locally.
After downloading Python3 zip follow instruciotn below
	1. tar -xvzf Python-3.5.0.tgz
	2. cd Python-3.5.0.tgz
	3. mkdir install
	4.  ./configure --with-ensurepip --prefix=<full path of current directory>/install/
	5. make -j4
	6. make install
	7. Update PATH to point to the bin directory of Python-3.5.0
		a. export PATH=/path/to/python/Python-3.5.0/install/bin:$PATH 
	8.  Install additional modules
	    a. python3 -m pip install numpy
	    b. python3 -m pip install matplotlib

Pipeline Script
You'll need to edit the pipeline scripts to correct the tools and data paths.
Move to pipeline script directory:
	cd /path/to/workflow_profiler

For the pipeline you would like to run 
	open the WES/WGS script 
		vi wgs_end2end_data_collection_gatk_best_practices.pl
	
	Edit the input file extenstion so that it matches your input file  extenstion so that it matches your input file
		# INPUT FASTQ FILES
		#OTHER FORMATS FOR FQ: "_1.fastq.gz; #"_1.fastq";
		my $fqFile1, $fqFile2;
		$fqFile1 = $inDataDir.$sample."_1.fq";
		$fqFile2 = $inDataDir.$sample."_2.fq";
		
	edit the broad, Queue, and homoref direcotry path relative to your computer.
		# Pipeline executables and its directories
		### ENTER THE CORRECT PATH TO THE FOLLOWING 3 VARIABLES ###
		my $broadDir = '/path/to/bioinformatic_tools_GATK_Picard_BWA';
		my $QueueBroadBestPracticesDir = '/path/to/Queue_Broad_BestPractices';
		my $homosapiensrefgenomeDir = '/path/to/homosapiensrefgenome';
	
Running the script
From the /path/to/workflow_profiler enter the command below to run the pipeline. 

python3 workflow_profiler.py <pipeline script to be run> gatk_best_practices <name of fastq files> <number of threads> <path to fastq files> <path for output files> -Ap


python3 workflow_profiler.py wgs_end2end_data_collection_gatk_best_practices_optimized.pl gatk_best_practices Solexa-272221 36 /home/opt/data/broadwgs/ /home/opt/data/broadout/ -Ap
